canonical:
  title: 謝賜鸚哥表
  author: 卞季良
  language: lzh
  text: 聖心仁厚庸篤撫綏寵賚稠重曷勝感激俯躬承命擧國騰懽竊念弊邦幸逢昭代唯謹歲時之禮未甞効勞每承優渥之榮寧不知愧又况能言之鳥出自重譯之邦是蓋養於禁園豈期分於荒服念前恩之難報而厚賜之荐臻玆盖伏遇敷大德以保民體至仁而育物遂令駑鈍獲被鴻私謹當常懷卵翼之私益虔侯度願獻乾坤之久恒祝皇齡
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 謝賜鸚哥表
  author: 卞季良
  language: lzh
  text: 聖心仁厚。庸篤撫綏。寵賚稠重。曷勝感激。俯躬承命。擧國騰懽。竊念弊邦。幸逢昭代。唯謹歲時之禮。未甞効勞。每承優渥之榮。寧不知愧。又况能言之鳥。出自重譯之邦。是蓋養於禁園。豈期分於荒服。念前恩之難報。而厚賜之荐臻。玆盖伏遇敷大德以保民。體至仁而育物。遂令駑鈍。獲被鴻私。謹當常懷卵翼之私。益虔侯度。願獻乾坤之久。恒祝皇齡。
korean:
  title: 앵무새의 하사를 사례하는 글
  author: 변계량
  language: kor
  text: 황제의 마음이 인후하셔서 돈독하게 먼 나라를 무유(撫綏)하시어, 하사하심이 중첩되오니 감격함을 어찌 이기리오. 몸을 꾸부려 명령을 받들매 온 나라가 기뻐하여 춤춥니다. 그윽이 생각하옵건대 소국은 다행히 좋은 시대를 만나서 오직 세시(歲時)의 조공만 삼가고, 일찍 공로를 바칠 것이 없는데 매양 우악한 영광을 받사오니 어찌 부끄러움을 알지 못하리이까. 또 하물며 말할 줄 아는 새는 멀고 먼 나라에서 왔으니, 이것은 대개 궁중 비원(秘苑)에 기를 것이라, 어찌 먼 지방에까지 나누어 주실 줄 알았겠습니까. 앞날의 은혜도 갚기 어려운데 어찌 후히 주심이 이르나이까. 이것은 대개 황제께서 큰 덕을 펴서 백성을 보존하고 천지의 지극한 인(仁)을 본받아, 만물을 육성하여서 드디어 우둔한 자로 하여금 큰 은혜를 입게 하심을 만난 것입니다.신은 삼가 마땅히 항상 덮어 주시고 기루어 주신 은혜를 생각하여, 더욱 제후(諸侯)의 법도를 삼가 지켜 천지의 장구함으로써, 항상 성수(聖壽)를 빌겠습니다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0410_010_0150&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: A Memorial Expressing Gratitude for the Gift of a Parrot
  author: Byeon Gyeryangnim
  language: eng
  text: 'Your Majesty''s heart flows with benevolence, gently nurturing the distant realm with steadfast care. Such abundant gifts pour forth—how can this humble subject contain such gratitude? Bowing low to receive your command, the entire nation leaps with joy. Yet I reflect: our small kingdom has been blessed to flourish in this enlightened age. We offer only the ritual tributes of the seasons, having no deeds of valor to present, and yet we constantly receive such generous honors. How can we not feel the weight of shame? And consider this talking bird—it comes from lands beyond the farthest translation, surely meant to dwell only within the imperial gardens. Who could have imagined it would reach even to remote borderlands? The former grace is already difficult to repay, and now these generous gifts arrive in succession. This flows from Your Majesty''s vast virtue that preserves the people, embodying the supreme compassion that nurtures all things. Thus even one as dull as I have been blessed with such magnanimous favor. I shall forever hold in reverent mind this debt of nurturing wings spread over me, ever more diligent in observing the protocols of a vassal state. With the permanence of heaven and earth, I shall eternally offer prayers for the longevity of the Sacred Life.'
  footnotes:
    - A 'memorial' or 'table' (表) was a formal diplomatic document submitted by tributary states to the Chinese court, expressing gratitude for imperial gifts or favors.
    - The 'talking bird' (parrot) was a luxury gift that demonstrated imperial favor and the tributary relationship between the Korean state and the Chinese throne.
    - '''Distant lands beyond translation'' refers to the notion that the parrot came from regions so remote that their languages required multiple layers of translation to be understood.'
